<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 2:26PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Newberry and northeastern Saluda Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 226 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Saluda, or 14 miles southwest of Newberry, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hollywood Elementary School, Stoney Hill, Scurry Airport, Wyses Ferry
and Hickory Grove.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
